 that the difference between the spinodals\nobtained within the pair approximation and the mean-field approach follows a\npower law with respect to $\\langle k\\rangle$, as long as the pair approximation\nindicates correctly the type of the phase transition.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 7 Jul 2021 16:26:57 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 16 Aug 2021 10:30:53 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-08-17"}
